Maybe next time,
you won't be so lucky.

792
00:40:39,900 --> 00:40:41,433
Is that understood?

793
00:40:41,900 --> 00:40:42,900
Good!

794
00:40:43,833 --> 00:40:45,167
Good thing
you have nothing to say.

795
00:40:45,900 --> 00:40:47,900
Are we done...
Miss Mckenna?

796
00:40:47,900 --> 00:40:49,833
Watch your tone, Miss Calaquian.

797
00:40:49,833 --> 00:40:50,833
[SCOFFS] Oh.

798
00:40:50,833 --> 00:40:53,933
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

799
00:40:53,933 --> 00:40:55,133
You're dismissed!

800
00:40:55,133 --> 00:40:56,767
And stay out of trouble!

801
00:40:59,200 --> 00:41:00,967
Oh, wait, Daphne.

802
00:41:04,067 --> 00:41:08,433
Leave my son alone.

803
00:41:15,033 --> 00:41:16,233
[LIGHTS SNAP OFF]

804
00:41:16,233 --> 00:41:18,133
- [NYX] Huh?
- [DAPHNE] Why...

805
00:41:18,133 --> 00:41:19,433
[NYX] Hello?

806
00:41:19,800 --> 00:41:24,000
[SCHOOL BELL RINGING]

807
00:41:27,100 --> 00:41:29,833
Why were you called
to the principal’s office?

808
00:41:30,933 --> 00:41:32,067
Why do you think?

809
00:41:33,767 --> 00:41:35,667
I'm not talking to you.

810
00:41:36,200 --> 00:41:38,000
I'm talking to my girlfriend.

811
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:40,767
You mean, ex-girlfriend?

812
00:41:44,900 --> 00:41:45,867
Marla...

813
00:41:46,200 --> 00:41:47,733
did you really do that?

814
00:41:49,833 --> 00:41:50,800
No.

815
00:41:59,233 --> 00:42:00,467
Marla!

816
00:42:01,533 --> 00:42:03,600
I don't wanna witness
all of this.

817
00:42:04,133 --> 00:42:05,100
Same.

818
00:42:05,100 --> 00:42:07,267
And this might turn
into World War III.

819
00:42:07,267 --> 00:42:08,733
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

820
00:42:12,767 --> 00:42:13,667
Can we talk?

821
00:42:14,900 --> 00:42:15,900
Fine.

822
00:42:17,700 --> 00:42:18,700
[LESTER SCOFFS]

823
00:42:20,567 --> 00:42:21,533
Babe.

824
00:42:22,633 --> 00:42:23,733
[LESTER EXHALES SHARPLY]

825
00:42:24,300 --> 00:42:26,600
You have been avoiding me
way too much.

826
00:42:26,600 --> 00:42:27,500
[DAPHNE SCOFFS]

827
00:42:27,500 --> 00:42:29,567
[LESTER] What?
Are you playing with me?

828
00:42:30,567 --> 00:42:31,433
[SCOFFS]

829
00:42:31,433 --> 00:42:33,867
- Because it's not funny.
- Oh, wow.

830
00:42:34,967 --> 00:42:37,567
Your mom said
I should leave you alone.

831
00:42:37,567 --> 00:42:39,900
For once, I agree with her.

832
00:42:39,900 --> 00:42:41,167
What the hell? What did you say?

833
00:42:41,167 --> 00:42:42,733
Oh, didn't you hear me?

834
00:42:43,600 --> 00:42:44,933
[SIGHS]

835
00:42:46,767 --> 00:42:49,100
Baby, please.

836
00:42:49,100 --> 00:42:50,267
Ignore her.

837
00:42:50,300 --> 00:42:51,733
Look...

838
00:42:51,733 --> 00:42:55,233
I don't care about the photos
or whatever my mom thinks.

839
00:42:55,233 --> 00:42:56,833
Just, please, give me a chance.

840
00:42:57,567 --> 00:42:58,900
Let's fix this. Please.

841
00:42:59,833 --> 00:43:01,067
You're insane!

842
00:43:01,067 --> 00:43:02,133
Just like your mom!

843
00:43:04,300 --> 00:43:05,300
[SIGHS SHARPLY]

844
00:43:06,867 --> 00:43:07,800
Babe!

845
00:43:12,233 --> 00:43:13,233
How are you?

846
00:43:14,000 --> 00:43:15,000
How are you holding up?

847
00:43:16,033 --> 00:43:17,200
Why do you ask?

848
00:43:17,833 --> 00:43:20,533
Nothing.
I'm just checking on you.

849
00:43:21,733 --> 00:43:23,700
I hope you're okay
after the breakup.

850
00:43:24,100 --> 00:43:25,567
Breakup.

851
00:43:25,967 --> 00:43:27,233
That’s just a cool-off, right?

852
00:43:28,300 --> 00:43:29,200
Right.

853
00:43:30,233 --> 00:43:32,700
Cool-off. Right.

854
00:43:33,600 --> 00:43:35,033
[SIGHS] Nyx...

855
00:43:37,267 --> 00:43:39,733
I just want to say
that our relationship

856
00:43:39,733 --> 00:43:41,267
was like a beautiful story.

857
00:43:41,833 --> 00:43:43,067
I'll always remember it.

858
00:43:44,067 --> 00:43:45,333
Even if we're not together.

859
00:43:46,267 --> 00:43:50,633
Our story continues
even if it does separately.

860
00:43:50,633 --> 00:43:52,967
Whatever.
That’s all you’re gonna say?

861
00:43:53,700 --> 00:43:55,633
Hmm... What else?

862
00:43:56,800 --> 00:43:59,400
Our story is like the ocean tide

863
00:43:59,400 --> 00:44:02,133
that flows and ebbs
with the ocean.

864
00:44:02,133 --> 00:44:03,267
Shh!

865
00:44:04,367 --> 00:44:06,900
Your poetic lines
won't work on me anymore.

866
00:44:07,267 --> 00:44:10,633
Stop it with your sweet talk.

867
00:44:11,133 --> 00:44:14,167
You think you can
fool me again, huh?

868
00:44:15,167 --> 00:44:17,067
You’re making me
even more pissed off.

869
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:19,667
Especially now.

870
00:44:20,300 --> 00:44:21,333
You're a liar.

871
00:44:24,167 --> 00:44:25,633
What do you mean?

872
00:44:25,633 --> 00:44:29,033
I need to know the whole truth

873
00:44:29,033 --> 00:44:31,767
and nothing but the truth,

874
00:44:31,800 --> 00:44:34,167
- so help me, Beyonce.
- Sorry.

875
00:44:34,167 --> 00:44:35,433
I still have class.

876
00:44:35,433 --> 00:44:36,867
I'll talk to you later.

877
00:44:41,067 --> 00:44:43,767
You asked to talk,
then you just walked out.

878
00:44:45,067 --> 00:44:46,000
Liar.

879
00:44:48,267 --> 00:44:49,233
[COLE] Marla.

880
00:44:49,800 --> 00:44:51,400
I'm sorry, I had to ask.

881
00:44:51,400 --> 00:44:53,233
Why would I do that?

882
00:44:53,900 --> 00:44:55,667
Tell me, why on earth

883
00:44:55,667 --> 00:44:58,333
would I take videos
of you and your friends while...

884
00:44:58,333 --> 00:44:59,667
doing it?

885
00:45:00,033 --> 00:45:01,367
Marla, sorry.

886
00:45:03,067 --> 00:45:06,033
I’m just thinking,
maybe you still blame me for...

887
00:45:06,033 --> 00:45:07,300
for your leaked photos.

888
00:45:08,267 --> 00:45:09,933
I already told you, right?

889
00:45:10,800 --> 00:45:12,433
I had nothing to do with that.

890
00:45:13,033 --> 00:45:16,100
I feel like
you're trying to get revenge.

891
00:45:16,933 --> 00:45:19,033
Sorry. I'm sorry
if that's what you think.

892
00:45:19,033 --> 00:45:21,033
Why would I do that?

893
00:45:21,033 --> 00:45:23,067
Especially if what you said
is true, right?

894
00:45:23,067 --> 00:45:24,800
You didn't do anything wrong.

895
00:45:25,867 --> 00:45:27,933
Also, why are you
even talking to me?

896
00:45:27,933 --> 00:45:29,167
We broke up, remember?

897
00:45:30,267 --> 00:45:31,233
Yeah.

898
00:45:33,867 --> 00:45:35,733
But I still care
about you, Marla.

899
00:45:37,333 --> 00:45:39,100
It won't go away.

900
00:45:40,733 --> 00:45:41,433
Please.

901
00:45:45,367 --> 00:45:46,367
That's sweet.

902
00:45:48,000 --> 00:45:48,967
Marla...

903
00:45:49,867 --> 00:45:50,900
I know...

904
00:45:50,900 --> 00:45:53,200
I know, I was the one
who broke up with you.

905
00:45:53,867 --> 00:45:55,467
But honestly, you know...

906
00:45:57,300 --> 00:45:58,800
I miss you so much.

907
00:45:59,900 --> 00:46:01,300
I am scared.

908
00:46:02,167 --> 00:46:04,167
I'm scared, I admit it.

909
00:46:04,500 --> 00:46:07,333
'Cause I don't know
how to handle the situation.

910
00:46:08,867 --> 00:46:12,033
But honestly, I hope you believe
what I'm about to say.

911
00:46:14,000 --> 00:46:15,333
I still love you so much.

912
00:46:15,333 --> 00:46:22,267
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

913
00:46:23,867 --> 00:46:25,133
If that's true...

914
00:46:26,167 --> 00:46:28,933
help me, let's find
the one who did this to me.

915
00:46:31,533 --> 00:46:34,200
I don't know
how this would help you.

916
00:46:34,200 --> 00:46:35,433
Marla, maybe...

917
00:46:36,233 --> 00:46:38,400
you need to heal and move on.

918
00:46:39,367 --> 00:46:41,900
Marla, you can't
keep living in the past.

919
00:46:41,900 --> 00:46:44,100
Especially if the past
keeps hurting you.

920
00:46:44,500 --> 00:46:47,100
Marla, please.
Give me a chance, Marla.

921
00:46:47,100 --> 00:46:49,000
It's so easy for you to say.

922
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:53,167
In case you haven't noticed,
my life is over!

923
00:46:54,100 --> 00:46:56,800
I lost my chances to get
a good scholarship abroad!

924
00:46:58,400 --> 00:47:00,067
And I even lost you.

925
00:47:03,100 --> 00:47:05,533
So you can't blame me
if I'm willing to do anything

926
00:47:05,533 --> 00:47:07,500
to find the one
who did this to me.

927
00:47:08,933 --> 00:47:10,167
Marla, please.

928
00:47:10,933 --> 00:47:13,300
Please, give me a chance.

929
00:47:13,833 --> 00:47:14,533
Come on.

930
00:47:15,933 --> 00:47:16,867
Please.

931
00:47:17,967 --> 00:47:18,967
Marla...

932
00:47:19,367 --> 00:47:21,300
I'm looking more
toward the future,

933
00:47:21,933 --> 00:47:23,467
and I see you there...

934
00:47:24,100 --> 00:47:25,133
with me.

935
00:47:26,500 --> 00:47:27,833
How is that possible?

936
00:47:29,467 --> 00:47:31,333
We're not even together
in the present,

937
00:47:31,933 --> 00:47:33,100
let alone the future.

938
00:47:35,567 --> 00:47:36,600
Marla!

939
00:47:36,600 --> 00:47:42,467
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

940
00:47:45,167 --> 00:47:47,067
Come on! Just like this.
Look at my face.

941
00:47:47,067 --> 00:47:48,233
I don't want it!

942
00:47:48,233 --> 00:47:50,500
- You're all making fun of me!
- Just go along with it!

943
00:47:50,533 --> 00:47:52,167
Just go with it!

944
00:47:52,500 --> 00:47:53,500
Come on!

945
00:47:53,500 --> 00:47:55,200
What is that? I hate this color!

946
00:47:55,200 --> 00:47:57,033
Come on! Don't be so picky!

947
00:47:57,033 --> 00:47:59,433
- [DAPHNE] That's why it's drag.
- I'm okay with all-black.

948
00:47:59,433 --> 00:48:00,600
[DAPHNE] Because it's fun!

949
00:48:00,600 --> 00:48:02,533
- [NYX] What all-black?
- [DAPHNE] You're so picky!

950
00:48:02,533 --> 00:48:04,533
[NYX] What's your peg? A witch?

951
00:48:04,533 --> 00:48:07,300
- [ISOBEL] What is on your face?
- [NYX] Come on, drag.

952
00:48:07,300 --> 00:48:09,067
- [DAPHNE] That suits her.
- [ISOBEL HUFFS]

953
00:48:09,067 --> 00:48:10,533
I swear,
If you touch my bangs,

954
00:48:10,533 --> 00:48:12,033
I will cut yours!

955
00:48:12,033 --> 00:48:13,433
[DAPHNE] Huh?
We don't even have bangs.

956
00:48:13,433 --> 00:48:16,467
No! I look like
Pink Pikachu. What is that?

957
00:48:17,000 --> 00:48:18,167
- [DAPHNE] Pikachu?
- [ISOBEL] No!

958
00:48:18,167 --> 00:48:19,233
- [DAPHNE] No, wait.
- [ISOBEL] Nyx.

959
00:48:19,233 --> 00:48:21,600
- [DAPHNE] Let's fix it.
- [ISOBEL] I can't, no.

960
00:48:21,600 --> 00:48:23,433
- What are we doing?
- [DAPHNE] You need to put...

961
00:48:23,467 --> 00:48:25,267
[ISOBEL] I know you guys
are gonna pick a pink shade.

962
00:48:25,267 --> 00:48:28,033
Either pick magenta, flamingo,
or freaking salmon.

963
00:48:28,033 --> 00:48:30,033
- Why is everything here?
- [NYX] This, it's salmon.

964
00:48:31,533 --> 00:48:32,900
Am I pretty there?

965
00:48:35,600 --> 00:48:36,567
Just okay.

966
00:48:40,133 --> 00:48:41,133
April...

967
00:48:42,900 --> 00:48:45,133
how are you? Are you okay?

968
00:48:47,900 --> 00:48:48,967
Just nervous.

969
00:48:49,600 --> 00:48:52,300
But we don't need
to have small talks

970
00:48:52,300 --> 00:48:54,233
about personal stuff.

971
00:48:54,233 --> 00:49:01,167
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

972
00:49:11,367 --> 00:49:12,367
April...

973
00:49:15,967 --> 00:49:17,167
I'm sorry.

974
00:49:18,533 --> 00:49:20,500
I didn't know it was like that
in your house.

975
00:49:21,500 --> 00:49:23,433
Every time I was there,

976
00:49:23,433 --> 00:49:25,067
it felt so calm.

977
00:49:26,100 --> 00:49:28,533
Maybe that’s also what Cole
is projecting onto me.

978
00:49:30,000 --> 00:49:32,700
And I thought it was normal
that you don't really get along,

979
00:49:32,700 --> 00:49:35,033
because that's how siblings
are sometimes.

980
00:49:36,000 --> 00:49:37,600
I didn't know it was...

981
00:49:38,733 --> 00:49:40,233
so hostile.

982
00:49:40,233 --> 00:49:42,033
We don't need
to be friends, Marla.

983
00:49:43,533 --> 00:49:44,667
I'm here because...

984
00:49:45,400 --> 00:49:48,300
we have a common experience
and a goal.

985
00:49:51,400 --> 00:49:54,200
But isn't that exactly
what a friend is?

986
00:49:55,433 --> 00:49:57,567
We share the same experiences.

987
00:49:57,567 --> 00:49:59,467
We share the same goal.

988
00:49:59,467 --> 00:50:01,000
And you don't know
it's my color!

989
00:50:01,000 --> 00:50:02,233
[MARLA] We're always together.

990
00:50:02,233 --> 00:50:03,467
I look like Pikachu!

991
00:50:04,167 --> 00:50:06,433
We're in this together.

992
00:50:06,733 --> 00:50:10,667
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

993
00:50:10,667 --> 00:50:12,167
Studying in SOSH,

994
00:50:13,000 --> 00:50:14,733
friendship is never a priority.

995
00:50:15,500 --> 00:50:17,067
Didn't you notice,

996
00:50:17,567 --> 00:50:20,333
there's no depth
in campus friendships.

997
00:50:21,133 --> 00:50:23,533
Everybody's too busy
studying and...

998
00:50:24,400 --> 00:50:25,967
surviving the program.

999
00:50:29,633 --> 00:50:31,067
Marla...

1000
00:50:32,233 --> 00:50:34,733
do you really not remember
what you did to me?

1001
00:50:37,067 --> 00:50:40,400
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

1002
00:50:40,400 --> 00:50:41,500
I do.

1003
00:50:44,500 --> 00:50:46,533
But I only did what was right.

1004
00:50:49,633 --> 00:50:51,033
Fair enough.

1005
00:50:51,533 --> 00:50:55,033
I mean, look at your big smile
in this photo.

1006
00:50:57,200 --> 00:51:01,533
So proud and
no sense of guilt at all.

1007
00:51:02,800 --> 00:51:03,767
[SIGHS]

1008
00:51:05,067 --> 00:51:06,167
Why?

1009
00:51:07,400 --> 00:51:09,100
Isn't that how
it's supposed to be?

1010
00:51:11,433 --> 00:51:13,167
Let me ask you this...

1011
00:51:14,133 --> 00:51:16,133
do you think you're doing
the right thing now?

1012
00:51:17,700 --> 00:51:24,700
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

1013
00:51:24,700 --> 00:51:25,833
Yes?

1014
00:51:25,833 --> 00:51:27,167
You're not sure.

1015
00:51:28,067 --> 00:51:29,333
That's hard, Marla.

1016
00:51:29,633 --> 00:51:31,600
We're in the middle of a battle.

1017
00:51:31,600 --> 00:51:34,700
You were sure when we tried
to expose the boys.

1018
00:51:35,467 --> 00:51:36,700
What changed now?

1019
00:51:39,067 --> 00:51:40,367
Well, I guess...

1020
00:51:41,467 --> 00:51:45,133
I realized that you shouldn't
hold on to anger.

1021
00:51:46,867 --> 00:51:48,300
Because when you're angry,

1022
00:51:48,300 --> 00:51:50,533
you can no longer tell
right from wrong.

1023
00:51:51,633 --> 00:51:52,767
Sometimes you don't know

1024
00:51:52,767 --> 00:51:55,567
if what you're doing
is still right or already wrong.

1025
00:51:57,700 --> 00:52:00,400
Also, I've never done
anything like this.

1026
00:52:01,300 --> 00:52:02,567
Ruin someone's life?

1027
00:52:02,833 --> 00:52:04,133
[MARLA] Yeah.

1028
00:52:05,267 --> 00:52:08,600
Well, you did ruin my life once.

1029
00:52:09,267 --> 00:52:10,700
But by doing the right thing.

1030
00:52:11,500 --> 00:52:12,700
So I suppose...

1031
00:52:12,700 --> 00:52:14,100
[INHALES]

1032
00:52:14,633 --> 00:52:16,767
...you're doing
the right thing now, Marla.

1033
00:52:17,567 --> 00:52:19,100
We're doing the right thing.

1034
00:52:21,667 --> 00:52:23,867
- [ISOBEL] Come on.
- [NYX] You're so picky.

1035
00:52:23,867 --> 00:52:26,467
[ISOBEL] I told you,
this is not my color palette.

1036
00:52:26,467 --> 00:52:29,133
[DAPHNE] What color palette
are you saying?

1037
00:52:29,133 --> 00:52:31,500
- [ISOBEL] I don't...
- [DAPHNE] This is blonde.

1038
00:52:31,500 --> 00:52:34,367
I wonder if Nyx knows
we're doing the right thing.

1039
00:52:34,733 --> 00:52:37,367
- This is just makeup. Look.
- [ISOBEL] I don't want!

1040
00:52:37,367 --> 00:52:39,433
You're all
making fun of me.

1041
00:52:39,433 --> 00:52:40,433
[NYX] Oh, you.

1042
00:52:40,433 --> 00:52:42,233
I guess we'll find out tonight.

1043
00:52:42,233 --> 00:52:43,700
Hurry. Girl, let's go!

1044
00:52:43,700 --> 00:52:46,633
We need to get ready
because it's already late.

1045
00:52:46,633 --> 00:52:47,633
Hurry!

1046
00:52:47,633 --> 00:52:49,333
[NYX] I'll iron that!

1047
00:52:49,333 --> 00:52:51,667
[ISOBEL] Why do I have to bring
freaking pink shades?

1048
00:52:51,700 --> 00:52:54,667
[DAPHNE] Come on.
Magenta, salmon, or baby pink...

1049
00:52:54,667 --> 00:52:55,800
- [ISOBEL] Salmon?!
- [NYX] What?

